# Golden-bundle fixture files must land on disk byte-for-byte identical on
# every platform, including Windows — their hashes are recorded in
# SHA256SUMS / index.json.content_hash, so any EOL translation from
# `core.autocrlf` breaks `verify_bundle`. Mark the whole fixture tree as
# binary to disable text normalization, filter, and diff attributes.
crates/cargo-evidence/tests/fixtures/golden-dev-bundle/** binary

# Compliance-report fixture is byte-compared by
# `tests/compliance_fixture.rs` — any EOL translation from
# `core.autocrlf` on Windows CI would flip LF→CRLF and break the
# comparison. Same binary treatment as the golden-bundle tree.
crates/evidence/tests/fixtures/compliance/** binary

# Source-tracked files whose bytes flow directly into the
# `deterministic_hash` projection. `cargo_lock_hash` is SHA-256 of
# `Cargo.lock`'s bytes; `rust_toolchain_toml` is the raw file
# content. On Windows with `core.autocrlf=true` (default), git checks
# these out with CRLF and their bytes drift from the Unix checkouts,
# breaking cross-host parity. Force LF everywhere so the three CI
# runners and any dev workstation see the same bytes.
Cargo.lock            text eol=lf
rust-toolchain.toml   text eol=lf

# PR #47 — golden wire-shape fixture. Keep literal bytes so cross-OS
# checkouts don't mangle line endings and trip the byte-diff test.
crates/cargo-evidence/tests/fixtures/golden_rules.json binary
